abstract: Learn how to build a minimalist game physics engine in Rust and make it accessible to Python developers using PyO3. This talk explores fundamental concepts like collision detection and motion dynamics while focusing on Python integration for scripting and testing. Ideal for developers interested in combining Rust’s performance with Python’s ease of use to create lightweight and efficient tools for games or simulations.
